git config --list


In VS Code : 
Create a file : abc.txt:
Hello world

save the file

The file becomes U : Un-commited

Now go to terminal:
 git add abc.txt

The file became : A (added in branch)



Now go to terminal:
 git commit -m "First commit : abc.txt"

The file gets commited


Now edit the file:
abc.txt:
Hello World
Modified Abc


save the file


The file became : M (Modified in branch, which was already comitted)

Now again add and commit with message "Second commit with modified abc.txt"


git clone clones the repository into our local current folder 
as a new folder with the same name as the repository name, with git initialized:

git clone https://github.com/monicag-gupta/Proj1.git


If SSH (https security) error occurs:

git -c http.sslVerify=false clone https://github.com/monicag-gupta/Proj1.git








